# Python Environment Standards

## Always Use uv for Package Management

```bash
# ✅ GOOD - Install packages with uv
uv pip install package-name
uv pip install -r requirements.txt

# ❌ BAD - Don't use pip directly
pip install package-name
```

## Always Activate .venv Before Running Python

```bash
# ✅ GOOD - Activate venv first
source .venv/bin/activate && python script.py

# Or use the venv python directly
.venv/bin/python script.py

# ❌ BAD - Running without venv
python script.py
```

## Quick Reference

- Install: `uv pip install <package>`
- Activate: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- Run: `python script.py` (after activation) or `.venv/bin/python script.py`
